======================================================================
KEY FINDING
======================================================================
After Bonferroni correction (×5), only the uncorrected Rayleigh test
remains significant (p_bonf = 0.040). All bias-corrected models
cross the α=0.05 threshold after correction:
  Model A: p_bonf = 0.115
  Model B: p_bonf = 0.445
  Model C: p_bonf = 0.890
  Model D: p_bonf = 1.000

CAVEAT: The four models test incommensurable null hypotheses and are
not exchangeable replicates. The Bonferroni correction is conservative
and provided for completeness only; the paper's central argument does
not rest on any single p-value crossing α=0.05, but on the range of
p-values across defensible methods.

